"a.健谈的；易旋转的 【考】 voluble : speech / licentious : dissoluteness(健谈的喜欢说话/放 荡的喜欢风流)maladroit : deft / voluble : terse(不灵巧对灵巧/健谈 对简洁)反义词: laconic(简明的); taciturn(沉默的); succinct(简洁的); reticent(沉默的) adj. 爱说话的; 健谈的 【类】voluble: speech = licentious: dissoluteness健谈的喜欢说话 = 放荡的喜欢风流maladroit: deft = voluble: terse不灵巧的不灵巧 = 健谈的不简洁 【反】laconic(adj 简明的); taciturn(adj 沉默的); succinct(adj 简洁的); reticent(adj 沉默的) 【记】voluble 易旋转的，健谈的，源自volv 转，脑瓜，嘴都转得快；volume 读了许多册书，能侃的 voluble (adj.)  early 15c., ""liable to constant change,"" from Middle French voluble, from Latin volubilis ""that turns around, rolling, flowing,"" figuratively (of speech) ""fluent, rapid,"" from volvere ""to turn around, roll"" (see volvox). Meaning ""fluent, talkative"" first recorded 1580s. Related: Volubly."
